BEGIN_PGML
Each point [`P`] on the unit circle is the terminal point for a certain angle [`t`], where [`0\leq t < 2\pi`] is measured in radians. 

Find [`t`] for these terminal points:
  
    (a) [` P(0,1) `], [`t=`] [_]{Compute("pi/2")}{15}; 
  
    (b) [` P(-\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2},\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}) `], [`t=`] [_]{Compute("3*pi/4")}{15}; 
  
    (c) [` P(-1,0) `], [`t=`] [_]{Compute("pi")}{15}; 
  
    (d) [` P(-\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2},-\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}) `], [`t=`] [_]{Compute("5*pi/4")}{15}; 
  
    (e) [` P(0,-1) `], [`t=`] [_]{Compute("3*pi/2")}{15}; 
  
    (f) [` P(\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2},-\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}) `], [`t=`] [_]{Compute("7*pi/4")}{15}. 
END_PGML

$ans1 = $PI/2;
$ans2 = 3*$PI/4;
$ans3 = $PI;
$ans4 = 5*$PI/4;
$ans5 = 3*$PI/2;
$ans6 = 7*$PI/4;

